- Always use WordPress coding standards when writing PHP.
- Follow PSR-4 naming conventions.
- Favor object-oriented programming.
- Add type hints for PHP code as much as possible.
- Optimize for readability.
- Compatible with PHP 7.2+ and WordPress 6.5+.
- Lint command: `phpcs`, format command: `phpcbf`.